  <graph edgedefault="undirected">
    <node id="Therapeutic Lifestyle Changes (TLC)">
      <data key="d0">Therapeutic Lifestyle Changes (TLC)</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">TLC is a foundation for clinical primary prevention that stresses reductions in saturated fat and cholesterol intakes.&lt;SEP&gt;TLC is a multifaceted lifestyle approach recommended by ATP III to reduce risk for CHD, involving dietary changes, increased physical activity, and weight reduction.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-57adaeb7bcb649de8c16646ccbd2da60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-07f4f68e34842231fc2bbe4c218d9f0e</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184625</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Clinical Primary Prevention">
      <data key="d0">Clinical Primary Prevention</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Clinical Primary Prevention is the initial stage of care where foundational lifestyle changes are emphasized.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-57adaeb7bcb649de8c16646ccbd2da60</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184625</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="LDL Cholesterol">
      <data key="d0">LDL Cholesterol</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">LDL cholesterol is a major target of cholesterol-lowering therapy; elevated levels are associated with Coronary Heart Disease.&lt;SEP&gt;LDL Cholesterol levels are the primary focus of risk assessment, determining goals for lowering therapy and classification risk.&lt;SEP&gt;LDL cholesterol is the primary target of therapy for reducing long-term risk, and its levels guide the intensity of risk-reduction therapy.&lt;SEP&gt;LDL cholesterol is a critical measured level that, when high or elevated, requires attention and monitoring.&lt;SEP&gt;LDL cholesterol is a key biomarker measured in persons, used to determine therapeutic requirements and risk levels.&lt;SEP&gt;A key biomarker that the TLC Diet aims to reduce, as its management is crucial for cardiovascular health.&lt;SEP&gt;Low-Density Lipoprotein, which is targeted for reduction to levels below 100 mg/dL in secondary prevention.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-57adaeb7bcb649de8c16646ccbd2da60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c570d0f2b907a96493872be58707aa5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed3e1f1eaf2900d92ba10f335113ce56&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-07f4f68e34842231fc2bbe4c218d9f0e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4d1e515ef00486628c0bb42b99da9cc4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d51c91a795e7cdcf59a9d0842dd49d94&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6bd98e2ff824d23b7b1224dc2e08b50a</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184625</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="LDL-lowering Drugs">
      <data key="d0">LDL-lowering Drugs</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">LDL-lowering drugs are a therapeutic option used for persons at higher risk to reduce major coronary events and coronary death.&lt;SEP&gt;LDL-lowering drugs are medications used to reduce LDL cholesterol levels in patients at higher risk.&lt;SEP&gt;LDL-lowering drugs are medical treatments considered for persons whose LDL cholesterol levels are elevated to achieve specific risk reduction goals.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-57adaeb7bcb649de8c16646ccbd2da60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-07f4f68e34842231fc2bbe4c218d9f0e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6bd98e2ff824d23b7b1224dc2e08b50a</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184625</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Major Coronary Events">
      <data key="d0">Major Coronary Events</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Major coronary events are severe cardiac incidents whose risk is reduced by LDL-lowering drugs.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-57adaeb7bcb649de8c16646ccbd2da60</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184625</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Coronary Death">
      <data key="d0">Coronary Death</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Coronary death is a type of cardiac fatality whose risk is reduced by LDL-lowering drugs.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-57adaeb7bcb649de8c16646ccbd2da60</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184625</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Secondary Dyslipidemia">
      <data key="d0">Secondary Dyslipidemia</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Secondary dyslipidemia is an abnormal lipid condition that must be ruled out before starting lipid-lowering therapy.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-57adaeb7bcb649de8c16646ccbd2da60</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184625</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Hyperlipidemia">
      <data key="d0">Hyperlipidemia</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Hyperlipidemia is a general condition characterized by elevated lipid levels.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-57adaeb7bcb649de8c16646ccbd2da60</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184625</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Diabetes">
      <data key="d0">Diabetes</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Diabetes is treated as a CHD risk equivalent within the ATP III classification guidelines.&lt;SEP&gt;Diabetes is identified as a potential cause of secondary dyslipidemia.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-57adaeb7bcb649de8c16646ccbd2da60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c570d0f2b907a96493872be58707aa5f</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184627</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Hypothyroidism">
      <data key="d0">Hypothyroidism</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Hypothyroidism is identified as a potential cause of secondary dyslipidemia.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-57adaeb7bcb649de8c16646ccbd2da60</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184627</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Obstructive Liver Disease">
      <data key="d0">Obstructive Liver Disease</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Obstructive liver disease is identified as a potential cause of secondary dyslipidemia.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-57adaeb7bcb649de8c16646ccbd2da60</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184627</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Chronic Renal Failure">
      <data key="d0">Chronic Renal Failure</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Chronic renal failure is identified as a potential cause of secondary dyslipidemia.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-57adaeb7bcb649de8c16646ccbd2da60</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184627</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Progestins, Anabolic Steroids, Corticosteroids">
      <data key="d0">Progestins, Anabolic Steroids, Corticosteroids</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">These drug types can increase LDL cholesterol and decrease HDL cholesterol, potentially causing secondary dyslipidemia.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-57adaeb7bcb649de8c16646ccbd2da60</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184628</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Secondary Prevention">
      <data key="d0">Secondary Prevention</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Secondary prevention focuses on managing and reducing risk for persons with established CHD.&lt;SEP&gt;The objective of drug therapy for CHD and CHD risk equivalents, aiming to attain low LDL cholesterol.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-57adaeb7bcb649de8c16646ccbd2da60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4d1e515ef00486628c0bb42b99da9cc4</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184628</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Total Mortality">
      <data key="d0">Total Mortality</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Total mortality is one of the outcomes reduced by LDL-lowering therapy in persons with established CHD.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-57adaeb7bcb649de8c16646ccbd2da60</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184628</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Coronary Heart Disease (CHD)">
      <data key="d0">Coronary Heart Disease (CHD)</data>
      <data key="d1">naturalobject</data>
      <data key="d2">CHD is a major cardiovascular risk that is strongly associated with elevated LDL cholesterol.&lt;SEP&gt;CHD is the established cardiovascular disease state for which LDL-lowering therapy is crucial.&lt;SEP&gt;A cardiovascular condition that requires secondary prevention and management of lipid risk factors.&lt;SEP&gt;CHD is a disease whose age-adjusted mortality rates declined in the United States between 1970 and 2000.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-57adaeb7bcb649de8c16646ccbd2da60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed3e1f1eaf2900d92ba10f335113ce56&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4d1e515ef00486628c0bb42b99da9cc4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-58763f1e533c69de4d39064f39a03154</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776186360</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="ATP III">
      <data key="d0">ATP III</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">ATP III is a set of classification guidelines used for determining goals and modalities for LDL-lowering therapy based on various risk factors.&lt;SEP&gt;ATP III is a body that specifies an optimal LDL cholesterol goal of &lt;100 mg/dL for secondary prevention.&lt;SEP&gt;ATP III is an assessment protocol that uses major risk factors to determine the core risk status.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-57adaeb7bcb649de8c16646ccbd2da60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c570d0f2b907a96493872be58707aa5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6bd98e2ff824d23b7b1224dc2e08b50a</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184628</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Metabolic Syndrome">
      <data key="d0">Metabolic Syndrome</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Metabolic syndrome is a set of multiple metabolic risk factors that identify persons for intensive therapeutic lifestyle changes.&lt;SEP&gt;A condition constituted by a constellation of major risk factors, life-habit risk factors, and emerging risk factors, characterized by abdominal obesity and dyslipidemia.&lt;SEP&gt;Metabolic syndrome is a cluster of risk factors, including elevated triglyceride or low HDL cholesterol.&lt;SEP&gt;Metabolic Syndrome is a health condition that requires attention to other lipid and nonlipid risk factors.&lt;SEP&gt;A health syndrome that requires management, with weight reduction being a primary therapeutic goal.&lt;SEP&gt;Metabolic Syndrome is a cluster of conditions that must be addressed within the framework of hypertension management.&lt;SEP&gt;Metabolic Syndrome is a condition whose estimated prevalence and relationship to adult treatment panels are analyzed in the provided tables.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-57adaeb7bcb649de8c16646ccbd2da60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed3e1f1eaf2900d92ba10f335113ce56&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-07f4f68e34842231fc2bbe4c218d9f0e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d51c91a795e7cdcf59a9d0842dd49d94&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6bd98e2ff824d23b7b1224dc2e08b50a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-089153c0a9e43f431c755dfee9cbc20e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2c68597b34118931dc76621ef26e8459</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776186294</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Saturated Fat and Cholesterol">
      <data key="d0">Saturated Fat and Cholesterol</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">These are dietary components that the TLC diet recommends reducing.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-57adaeb7bcb649de8c16646ccbd2da60</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184629</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="LDL Cholesterol Goal">
      <data key="d0">LDL Cholesterol Goal</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">The LDL Cholesterol Goal represents specific cutpoints used to determine the necessary intensity of lipid-lowering therapy.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-57adaeb7bcb649de8c16646ccbd2da60</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184629</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="TLC Diet">
      <data key="d0">TLC Diet</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">The TLC Diet is a dietary regimen that stresses reductions in saturated fat and cholesterol intakes.&lt;SEP&gt;TLC Diet is a recommended first-line therapeutic approach involving dietary modifications aimed at managing LDL cholesterol.&lt;SEP&gt;The TLC Diet is a structured nutritional intervention designed to manage cardiovascular health by controlling specific nutrient intakes.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-57adaeb7bcb649de8c16646ccbd2da60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-07f4f68e34842231fc2bbe4c218d9f0e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d51c91a795e7cdcf59a9d0842dd49d94</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184629</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Optimal LDL Cholesterol Level">
      <data key="d0">Optimal LDL Cholesterol Level</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">An LDL cholesterol level of &lt;100 mg/dL is considered optimal for secondary prevention.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-57adaeb7bcb649de8c16646ccbd2da60</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184629</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Total Cholesterol">
      <data key="d0">Total Cholesterol</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">Total cholesterol is a measured component of the lipoprotein profile recommended for initial testing.&lt;SEP&gt;Total Cholesterol levels are used in classification to determine risk categories and guide management goals.&lt;SEP&gt;Total cholesterol is a risk factor used in the Framingham scoring system for 10-year risk assessment.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c570d0f2b907a96493872be58707aa5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed3e1f1eaf2900d92ba10f335113ce56&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6bd98e2ff824d23b7b1224dc2e08b50a</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184630</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="HDL Cholesterol">
      <data key="d0">HDL Cholesterol</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">HDL cholesterol is a measured component of the lipoprotein profile, with classification recommendations updated in ATP III.&lt;SEP&gt;HDL Cholesterol levels are used in classification to determine risk categories and guide management goals.&lt;SEP&gt;HDL cholesterol is a component of atherogenic dyslipidemia and is recognized as a factor in metabolic syndrome.&lt;SEP&gt;HDL cholesterol is a biomarker, and low levels suggest the need for specific lipid-modifying treatments.&lt;SEP&gt;HDL cholesterol is a biomarker that can be raised by consuming a higher intake of unsaturated fat.&lt;SEP&gt;High-Density Lipoprotein, which is targeted for an increase to levels of 3-5%.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c570d0f2b907a96493872be58707aa5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed3e1f1eaf2900d92ba10f335113ce56&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-07f4f68e34842231fc2bbe4c218d9f0e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4d1e515ef00486628c0bb42b99da9cc4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d51c91a795e7cdcf59a9d0842dd49d94&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6bd98e2ff824d23b7b1224dc2e08b50a</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184630</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="CHD">
      <data key="d0">CHD</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">CHD stands for coronary heart disease, representing the major health condition whose risk level is being assessed and modified.&lt;SEP&gt;CHD stands for Coronary Heart Disease and represents the long-term risk outcome targeted by therapeutic interventions.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c570d0f2b907a96493872be58707aa5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-07f4f68e34842231fc2bbe4c218d9f0e</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184630</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Framingham Risk Scores">
      <data key="d0">Framingham Risk Scores</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">The Framingham risk scores are a method used to estimate the 10-year CHD risk for persons with multiple risk factors.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c570d0f2b907a96493872be58707aa5f</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184630</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Cigarette Smoking">
      <data key="d0">Cigarette Smoking</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Cigarette smoking is listed as a major risk factor that contributes to the modification of LDL goals.&lt;SEP&gt;Cigarette smoking is identified as a major, modifiable risk factor for CHD.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c570d0f2b907a96493872be58707aa5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6bd98e2ff824d23b7b1224dc2e08b50a</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184630</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Hypertension">
      <data key="d0">Hypertension</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Hypertension is a major risk factor, defined by a blood pressure reading of $\ge$ 140/90 mmHg or use of antihypertensive medication.&lt;SEP&gt;Hypertension is the central condition being evaluated and managed throughout the document.&lt;SEP&gt;Hypertension is the specific focus of the committee's reports, detailing its causes, classifications, and various forms of treatment.&lt;SEP&gt;Hypertension is the primary medical condition addressed throughout the report, concerning high blood pressure.&lt;SEP&gt;Hypertension is the medical condition the guidelines aim to prevent, detect, and treat.&lt;SEP&gt;Hypertension is a common medical condition whose prevalence, awareness, treatment, and control were monitored by national surveys and global organizations.&lt;SEP&gt;Hypertension is a common condition in the United States, often uncontrolled and undiagnosed, which places strain on healthcare.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c570d0f2b907a96493872be58707aa5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-089153c0a9e43f431c755dfee9cbc20e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2c68597b34118931dc76621ef26e8459&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-58763f1e533c69de4d39064f39a03154&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0aa33a009726cb2a0f199d167ecc8006&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a158d7acb0688d684776ba9a5ab0bfa4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-52224da6ee438f52167a3af07f7ae220&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b156f8826fe2c8e9404ae230c7ef768c</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776186294</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Family History of Premature CHD">
      <data key="d0">Family History of Premature CHD</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">This is a major risk factor identified by the occurrence of CHD in a first-degree relative under specific age limits.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c570d0f2b907a96493872be58707aa5f</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184631</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Age">
      <data key="d0">Age</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Age is a major risk factor used in conjunction with other measurements to assess 10-year CHD risk.&lt;SEP&gt;Age is recognized as a major risk factor for CHD in the Framingham scoring system.&lt;SEP&gt;Age in years of the patient.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c570d0f2b907a96493872be58707aa5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6bd98e2ff824d23b7b1224dc2e08b50a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-447c6e3389a31a2f5b30a6feff63926e</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776185120</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Atherosclerotic Disease">
      <data key="d0">Atherosclerotic Disease</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">Atherosclerotic disease includes other clinical forms such as peripheral arterial disease, abdominal aortic aneurysm, and symptomatic carotid artery disease.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c570d0f2b907a96493872be58707aa5f</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184631</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Peripheral Arterial Disease">
      <data key="d0">Peripheral Arterial Disease</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Peripheral arterial disease is cited as one of the clinical forms of atherosclerotic disease.&lt;SEP&gt;This topic addresses peripheral arterial disease as a component of metabolic health risks.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c570d0f2b907a96493872be58707aa5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b156f8826fe2c8e9404ae230c7ef768c</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776186437</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Abdominal Aortic Aneurysm">
      <data key="d0">Abdominal Aortic Aneurysm</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">Abdominal aortic aneurysm is cited as one of the clinical forms of atherosclerotic disease.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c570d0f2b907a96493872be58707aa5f</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184631</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Symptomatic Carotid Artery Disease">
      <data key="d0">Symptomatic Carotid Artery Disease</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">Symptomatic carotid artery disease is cited as one of the clinical forms of atherosclerotic disease.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c570d0f2b907a96493872be58707aa5f</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184631</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="National Cholesterol Education Program">
      <data key="d0">National Cholesterol Education Program</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">The National Cholesterol Education Program is the body responsible for creating updated clinical guidelines for high blood cholesterol.&lt;SEP&gt;The National Cholesterol Education Program is an expert panel responsible for guidelines on the detection, evaluation, and treatment of high blood cholesterol in adults.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-6a0733bca7611147bd0d7b8452e9cd47&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed3e1f1eaf2900d92ba10f335113ce56</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184632</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="National Heart, Lung, and Blood Institute">
      <data key="d0">National Heart, Lung, and Blood Institute</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">The National Heart, Lung, and Blood Institute (NHLBI) is a federal entity providing guidelines and being subject to public laws regarding non-discrimination.&lt;SEP&gt;The National Heart, Lung, and Blood Institute is a member contributing to the report.&lt;SEP&gt;This institute is one of the member organizations contributing to the report.&lt;SEP&gt;This Institute supported the work and provided financial backing for the report.&lt;SEP&gt;The National Heart, Lung, and Blood Institute is a major federal institute concerning cardiovascular and pulmonary health.&lt;SEP&gt;The National Heart, Lung, and Blood Institute is the institution that prepared and published reports on cardiovascular, lung, and blood diseases.&lt;SEP&gt;This institute prepared data detailing the percent decline in age-adjusted mortality rates for stroke and coronary heart disease.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-6a0733bca7611147bd0d7b8452e9cd47&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4417d5a880fb11a8f66ef7c4eb00233a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d96a06cecd736cbf1db97a308bbdfd7a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d325d60dfcf15b69e0c3889a048bbf73&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-58763f1e533c69de4d39064f39a03154&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-52224da6ee438f52167a3af07f7ae220</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776186281</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="National Institutes of Health">
      <data key="d0">National Institutes of Health</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">The National Institutes of Health (NIH) is a governmental organization associated with publishing the guidelines.&lt;SEP&gt;The National Institutes of Health provided support for the production of the guideline reports.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-6a0733bca7611147bd0d7b8452e9cd47&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d325d60dfcf15b69e0c3889a048bbf73</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776186284</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="High Blood Cholesterol">
      <data key="d0">High Blood Cholesterol</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">High blood cholesterol is a medical condition that is the focus of updated clinical guidelines for detection and treatment.&lt;SEP&gt;High Blood Cholesterol is the medical condition that the NCEP Expert Panel addressed in its reports.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-6a0733bca7611147bd0d7b8452e9cd47&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed3e1f1eaf2900d92ba10f335113ce56</data>
