      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Linda Van Horn, Ph.D., R.D.">
      <data key="d0">Linda Van Horn, Ph.D., R.D.</data>
      <data key="d1">person</data>
      <data key="d2">Linda Van Horn is the representative from the American Dietetic Association.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-4417d5a880fb11a8f66ef7c4eb00233a</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184641</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Third Report of the Expert Panel on Detection, Evaluation, and Treatment of High Blood Cholesterol in Adults (Adult Treatment Panel III) (ATP III)">
      <data key="d0">Third Report of the Expert Panel on Detection, Evaluation, and Treatment of High Blood Cholesterol in Adults (Adult Treatment Panel III) (ATP III)</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">ATP III constitutes updated clinical guidelines for cholesterol testing and management, building on previous ATP reports.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ed3e1f1eaf2900d92ba10f335113ce56</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184641</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Triglycerides">
      <data key="d0">Triglycerides</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">Triglycerides are a measured component of the lipoprotein profile, requiring attention if moderately elevated.&lt;SEP&gt;Triglycerides are a lipid risk factor that can be reduced by consuming total fat, especially unsaturated fat.&lt;SEP&gt;Measures the level of TG, which is targeted for reduction (e.g., below 200 mg/dL).</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ed3e1f1eaf2900d92ba10f335113ce56&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4d1e515ef00486628c0bb42b99da9cc4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d51c91a795e7cdcf59a9d0842dd49d94</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184641</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Lipoprotein Profile">
      <data key="d0">Lipoprotein Profile</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">The Lipoprotein Profile is the preferred initial test that measures total cholesterol, LDL, HDL, and triglycerides.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ed3e1f1eaf2900d92ba10f335113ce56</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184641</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Framingham Projections">
      <data key="d0">Framingham Projections</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Framingham projections utilize 10-year absolute CHD risk to identify patients with multiple risk factors needing intensive treatment.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ed3e1f1eaf2900d92ba10f335113ce56</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184641</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="ATP I">
      <data key="d0">ATP I</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">ATP I outlined a strategy for primary prevention of Coronary Heart Disease (CHD) in persons with high or borderline-high LDL cholesterol.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ed3e1f1eaf2900d92ba10f335113ce56</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184642</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="ATP II">
      <data key="d0">ATP II</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">ATP II affirmed the importance of primary prevention and added the intensive management of LDL cholesterol in persons with established CHD.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ed3e1f1eaf2900d92ba10f335113ce56</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184642</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Plant Stanols/Sterols">
      <data key="d0">Plant Stanols/Sterols</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">Plant stanols/sterols are recommended therapeutic dietary options for enhancing the lowering of LDL cholesterol.&lt;SEP&gt;Plant stanols/sterols are a therapeutic option for enhancing LDL lowering, recommended at a dosage of 2 g/day.&lt;SEP&gt;These are therapeutic options for lowering LDL cholesterol, recommended for adding to the diet if goals are not met.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ed3e1f1eaf2900d92ba10f335113ce56&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-07f4f68e34842231fc2bbe4c218d9f0e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d51c91a795e7cdcf59a9d0842dd49d94</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184642</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Viscous Fiber">
      <data key="d0">Viscous Fiber</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">Viscous (soluble) fiber is recommended as a therapeutic dietary option for lowering LDL cholesterol.&lt;SEP&gt;Viscous (soluble) fiber is a dietary element recommended for enhancing LDL lowering, with a target intake of 10-25 g/day.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ed3e1f1eaf2900d92ba10f335113ce56&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-07f4f68e34842231fc2bbe4c218d9f0e</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184642</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Nicotinic Acid">
      <data key="d0">Nicotinic Acid</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">Nicotinic Acid is an example of a lipid-modifying drug that can be used if a patient has elevated triglyceride or low HDL cholesterol.&lt;SEP&gt;A drug available in immediate, extended, and sustained release forms, used in lipid and metabolic management.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-07f4f68e34842231fc2bbe4c218d9f0e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4d1e515ef00486628c0bb42b99da9cc4</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184643</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Fibric Acid">
      <data key="d0">Fibric Acid</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">Fibric Acid is an example of a lipid-modifying drug used in the treatment of other lipid or nonlipid risk factors.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-07f4f68e34842231fc2bbe4c218d9f0e</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184643</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Triglyceride">
      <data key="d0">Triglyceride</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">Triglyceride is a biomarker, and elevated levels suggest the need for specific lipid-modifying treatments.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-07f4f68e34842231fc2bbe4c218d9f0e</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184643</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="10-Year Risk">
      <data key="d0">10-Year Risk</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">The 10-Year Risk is a calculated measure used to determine the intensity of required therapy for managing cardiovascular risk.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-07f4f68e34842231fc2bbe4c218d9f0e</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184643</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Coronary Atherosclerosis">
      <data key="d0">Coronary Atherosclerosis</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Coronary Atherosclerosis is a development that drug therapy aims to slow down, reducing long-term risk.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-07f4f68e34842231fc2bbe4c218d9f0e</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184643</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Saturated Fats">
      <data key="d0">Saturated Fats</data>
      <data key="d1">naturalobject</data>
      <data key="d2">Saturated fats are a nutrient that should be reduced in intake, specifically recommended to be less than 7% of total calories.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-07f4f68e34842231fc2bbe4c218d9f0e</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184643</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Cholesterol">
      <data key="d0">Cholesterol</data>
      <data key="d1">naturalobject</data>
      <data key="d2">Cholesterol is a key nutrient marker and dietary component, with recommended intake levels guidelines provided for dietary management.&lt;SEP&gt;Cholesterol intake must be kept below 200 mg/day as part of the TLC Diet.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-07f4f68e34842231fc2bbe4c218d9f0e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d51c91a795e7cdcf59a9d0842dd49d94</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184644</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Clinical Judgment">
      <data key="d0">Clinical Judgment</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Clinical judgment is required when applying therapy guidelines, particularly for older persons, to consider various factors like concomitant illnesses and general health status.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-07f4f68e34842231fc2bbe4c218d9f0e</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184644</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Statin Drugs">
      <data key="d0">Statin Drugs</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">A class of drugs, including lovastatin, pravastatin, simvastatin, fluvastatin, atorvastatin, and cerivastatin, used in lipid management.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-4d1e515ef00486628c0bb42b99da9cc4</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184644</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Bile Acid Sequestrants">
      <data key="d0">Bile Acid Sequestrants</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">A class of drugs available for lowering LDL cholesterol, which binds with bile acids in the gastrointestinal tract.&lt;SEP&gt;A class of agents, including cholestyramine, colestipol, and colesevelam, used to reduce major intestinal bile acid secretion.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-4d1e515ef00486628c0bb42b99da9cc4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d51c91a795e7cdcf59a9d0842dd49d94</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184644</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Fibrates">
      <data key="d0">Fibrates</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">A class of drugs, including gemfibrozil, fenofibrate, and clofibrate, used in lipid management.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-4d1e515ef00486628c0bb42b99da9cc4</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184644</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Hyperuricemia">
      <data key="d0">Hyperuricemia</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Elevated uric acid levels, which are associated with the risk of severe gout.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-4d1e515ef00486628c0bb42b99da9cc4</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184644</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Hepatotoxicity">
      <data key="d0">Hepatotoxicity</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">A potential side effect or risk associated with drug usage.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-4d1e515ef00486628c0bb42b99da9cc4</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184645</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Food and Drug Administration (FDA)">
      <data key="d0">Food and Drug Administration (FDA)</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">The governmental body responsible for allowing medications to become over-the-counter (OTC) drugs.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-4d1e515ef00486628c0bb42b99da9cc4</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184645</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Peptic Ulcer Disease">
      <data key="d0">Peptic Ulcer Disease</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">A potential gastrointestinal complication associated with drug use.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-4d1e515ef00486628c0bb42b99da9cc4</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184645</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Dyspepsia">
      <data key="d0">Dyspepsia</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Indigestion symptoms that can result from the use of various drugs.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-4d1e515ef00486628c0bb42b99da9cc4</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184645</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Myopathy">
      <data key="d0">Myopathy</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">A muscular condition listed as a potential complication of certain drug types.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-4d1e515ef00486628c0bb42b99da9cc4</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184646</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Cytochrome P-450 Inhibitors">
      <data key="d0">Cytochrome P-450 Inhibitors</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">A category of drugs that requires caution when used with fibrates and niacin due to metabolic interactions.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-4d1e515ef00486628c0bb42b99da9cc4</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184646</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Gastrointestinal Distress">
      <data key="d0">Gastrointestinal Distress</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">General discomfort or issues related to the digestive tract, specifically mentioned in relation to bile acid binding.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-4d1e515ef00486628c0bb42b99da9cc4</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184706</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Viscous (Soluble) Fiber">
      <data key="d0">Viscous (Soluble) Fiber</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">This nutrient is recommended for dietary intake to help lower LDL cholesterol.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d51c91a795e7cdcf59a9d0842dd49d94</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184706</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Saturated Fat">
      <data key="d0">Saturated Fat</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Saturated fat intake must be reduced significantly when initiating the TLC Diet.&lt;SEP&gt;Reduced intake of saturated fat is a key component of the public health approach to primary prevention.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d51c91a795e7cdcf59a9d0842dd49d94&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6bd98e2ff824d23b7b1224dc2e08b50a</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184706</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Polyunsaturated Fat">
      <data key="d0">Polyunsaturated Fat</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Polyunsaturated fat is a nutrient that the TLC Diet recommends maintaining up to 10% of total calories.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d51c91a795e7cdcf59a9d0842dd49d94</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184706</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Monounsaturated Fat">
      <data key="d0">Monounsaturated Fat</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Monounsaturated fat is a nutrient that the TLC Diet recommends maintaining up to 20% of total calories.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d51c91a795e7cdcf59a9d0842dd49d94</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184707</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Total Fat">
      <data key="d0">Total Fat</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Total fat intake is allowed to range from 25-35% of total calories, provided saturated fats are low.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d51c91a795e7cdcf59a9d0842dd49d94</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184707</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Carbohydrate">
      <data key="d0">Carbohydrate</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Carbohydrate intake should account for 50-60% of total calories and should predominantly come from complex sources.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d51c91a795e7cdcf59a9d0842dd49d94</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184707</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Fiber">
      <data key="d0">Fiber</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Fiber intake is recommended at 20-30 g/day as part of the TLC Diet.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d51c91a795e7cdcf59a9d0842dd49d94</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184707</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Protein">
      <data key="d0">Protein</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Protein intake should account for approximately 15% of total calories.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d51c91a795e7cdcf59a9d0842dd49d94</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184707</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Total Calories (Energy)">
      <data key="d0">Total Calories (Energy)</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The goal regarding total calories is to balance energy intake and expenditure to maintain desirable body weight.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d51c91a795e7cdcf59a9d0842dd49d94</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184707</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Overweight And Obese">
      <data key="d0">Overweight And Obese</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">This is a state of the population that requires weight reduction therapy and comprehensive management.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d51c91a795e7cdcf59a9d0842dd49d94</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184708</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Weight Reduction Therapy">
      <data key="d0">Weight Reduction Therapy</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Weight reduction therapy is recommended for overweight or obese patients, enhancing LDL lowering and overall health.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d51c91a795e7cdcf59a9d0842dd49d94</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184708</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Dietary Guidelines For Americans 2000">
      <data key="d0">Dietary Guidelines For Americans 2000</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">These guidelines provide the foundational recommendations for the TLC Diet, with one exception for total fat range.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d51c91a795e7cdcf59a9d0842dd49d94</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184708</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Physical Activity">
      <data key="d0">Physical Activity</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Physical activity, including moderate activity, is encouraged to improve overall health and assist in weight management.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d51c91a795e7cdcf59a9d0842dd49d94</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184708</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Registered Dietitians">
      <data key="d0">Registered Dietitians</data>
      <data key="d1">person</data>
      <data key="d2">Registered Dietitians are qualified nutrition professionals who are recommended for medical nutrition therapy.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d51c91a795e7cdcf59a9d0842dd49d94</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184709</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="HMG CoA Reductase Inhibitors">
      <data key="d0">HMG CoA Reductase Inhibitors</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">A class of drugs available for lowering LDL cholesterol, such as statins, with various potential side effects.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d51c91a795e7cdcf59a9d0842dd49d94</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184709</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Transfatty Acids">
      <data key="d0">Transfatty Acids</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Transfatty acids are a type of fat that raises LDL cholesterol and must be kept at a low intake.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d51c91a795e7cdcf59a9d0842dd49d94</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184709</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Complex Carbohydrates">
      <data key="d0">Complex Carbohydrates</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">Complex carbohydrates, which include whole grains, fruits, and vegetables, are the preferred source for carbohydrate intake.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d51c91a795e7cdcf59a9d0842dd49d94</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184709</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Nutritionist">
      <data key="d0">Nutritionist</data>
      <data key="d1">person</data>
      <data key="d2">A qualified nutrition professional, who, along with registered dietitians, can provide medical nutrition therapy.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d51c91a795e7cdcf59a9d0842dd49d94</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184709</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Framingham Scoring">
      <data key="d0">Framingham Scoring</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Framingham Scoring is a method used for 10-year risk assessment for Coronary Heart Disease (CHD) that considers multiple risk factors.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-6bd98e2ff824d23b7b1224dc2e08b50a</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184709</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Blood Pressure">
      <data key="d0">Blood Pressure</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Blood pressure is listed as a major risk factor used in scoring systems for CHD.&lt;SEP&gt;Blood Pressure is a measurable vital sign, the control of which is central to the report's recommendations.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-6bd98e2ff824d23b7b1224dc2e08b50a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a158d7acb0688d684776ba9a5ab0bfa4</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776186371</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="10-year Risk for CHD">
      <data key="d0">10-year Risk for CHD</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">The 10-year risk for CHD is divided into three categories: &gt;20%, 10-20%, and &lt;10%, assessed by Framingham scoring.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-6bd98e2ff824d23b7b1224dc2e08b50a</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184710</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Core Risk Status">
      <data key="d0">Core Risk Status</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The core risk status is the initial risk assessment determined by major risk factors in ATP III.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-6bd98e2ff824d23b7b1224dc2e08b50a</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184710</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Life-Habit Risk Factors">
      <data key="d0">Life-Habit Risk Factors</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">These are direct targets for clinical intervention and include obesity, physical inactivity, and atherogenic diet.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-6bd98e2ff824d23b7b1224dc2e08b50a</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184710</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Emerging Risk Factors">
      <data key="d0">Emerging Risk Factors</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">These risk factors include lipoprotein (a), homocysteine, and proinflammatory factors, and they contribute to CHD risk.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-6bd98e2ff824d23b7b1224dc2e08b50a</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184710</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Primary Prevention">
      <data key="d0">Primary Prevention</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Primary prevention is a public health approach aimed at reducing the overall burden of CHD through lifestyle changes.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-6bd98e2ff824d23b7b1224dc2e08b50a</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184710</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Obesity">
      <data key="d0">Obesity</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Obesity is a life-habit risk factor and a characteristic component of the Metabolic Syndrome.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-6bd98e2ff824d23b7b1224dc2e08b50a</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776184711</data>
