    <edge source="Therapeutic Lifestyle Changes (TLC)" target="Drug Therapy">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">TLC and drug therapy are presented as two major modalities for LDL-lowering therapy.</data>
      <data key="d9">alternative treatment,modalities</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-57adaeb7bcb649de8c16646ccbd2da60</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d12">1776184714</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="LDL Cholesterol" target="Secondary Dyslipidemia">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">Elevated or elevated LDL cholesterol levels require assessment to rule out secondary dyslipidemia.</data>
      <data key="d9">assessment,risk factor screening</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-57adaeb7bcb649de8c16646ccbd2da60</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d12">1776184713</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="LDL Cholesterol" target="ATP III">
      <data key="d7">2.0</data>
      <data key="d8">The ATP III guidelines establish the classification and corresponding goals for LDL cholesterol levels.&lt;SEP&gt;ATP III specifies an optimal LDL cholesterol goal of &lt;100 mg/dL for secondary prevention.</data>
      <data key="d9">goal setting,optimal treatment,risk classification</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-57adaeb7bcb649de8c16646ccbd2da60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c570d0f2b907a96493872be58707aa5f</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d12">1776184714</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="LDL Cholesterol" target="Optimal LDL Cholesterol Level">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">The optimal LDL cholesterol level is set at &lt;100 mg/dL&gt; for secondary prevention.</data>
      <data key="d9">benchmark,clinical guidance</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-57adaeb7bcb649de8c16646ccbd2da60</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d12">1776184715</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="LDL Cholesterol" target="Major Risk Factors">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">Multiple major risk factors, excluding LDL cholesterol, are used to modify the goals for LDL-lowering treatment.</data>
      <data key="d9">risk modification,therapy goal definition</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-c570d0f2b907a96493872be58707aa5f</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d12">1776184716</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="LDL Cholesterol" target="Multiple Risk Factors">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">The presence of multiple risk factors (2+) modifies the LDL cholesterol goal, setting the target at &lt;130 mg/dL.</data>
